The paper discusses the security vulnerabilities of wireless connectivity in implantable medical devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the design specifications and recommendations for developing comprehensive zero-power defense solutions, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC), system and control theory (cs.SY), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and software engineering (cs.SE).
